718399f-a.text:
Central Park: Sailboat Pool, Fifth Avenue from 72nd to 73rd Streets
in the background.
The middle apartment building, 912 Fifth Avenue, is the newest of the
three, replacing two old mansions.
May 17, 1933.
P. L  . Sperr.

718402f-b.text:
Central Park: A set of 3 views eastward across the Sailboat Pool (also known as Conservatory Lake) to Fifth Ave. and showing buildings upon the east side of the latter, between East 74th (left) and East
72nd (right) Streets.
May 2, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

Central Park : The cherry blossoms in the easterly side of Ehe Park. Buildings appearing across same are on Fiftyg Avenue, extending from 74th Street on the left to 72nd Street
